refsection.para:
In the following example, we compute the probability of the event S=2
for the negative binomial distribution function with Xn=3,
Pr=0.7 and Ompr=0.3.

refsection.programlisting:
S = 2;
Xn = 3;
Pr = 0.7;
Ompr = 0.3;
// Expected : P = 0.83692 and Q = 1-P
[P, Q] = cdfnbn("PQ", S, Xn, Pr, Ompr)
